{"questionId":"27675","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider a three-digit code <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mi>c</mi></math>, where each of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math> is assigned one of&nbsp;the values <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math>, where each of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math> is assigned one of&nbsp;the values <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math>. Assume that no value is repeated.</p>\n<p>Consider the case where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> has a factor of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find an expression for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>correct use of factor theorem for at least one of their factors&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; or&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p>attempt to find two equations in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>⇒</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>b</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;and&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to combine their two equations in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>b</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;to eliminate <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award at most <em><strong>A1M1M1A0M1A0</strong></em> for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></math>&nbsp;from&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>P</mi><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to compare coefficients of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>d</mi></math>&nbsp; and&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>d</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to eliminate&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 3</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to divide&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math>&nbsp;by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>c</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><br>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></math>, <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;and <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn></math></p>\n<p><br>recognition that, if&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;is a factor of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>, then&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>leading to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 4</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to use Vieta’s formulae for a cubic with roots&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;and \"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>\"&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>⇒</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>b</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>Attempt to eliminate&nbsp;\"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>\"&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>b</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award at most <em><strong>A1M1A0A0M1A0</strong></em> for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></math>&nbsp;from roots&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;\"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>\"&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27675","referenceCode":"22N.1.AHL.TZ0.11b.i","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find an expression for b in terms of a.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.3—Graphing","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.4—Key features of graphs, intersections using technology","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.12—Factor and remainder theorems, sum and product of roots"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}